WEBVTT

00:10.810 --> 00:12.505
HOLMES:
Watson, I've gone to a meeting.

00:12.540 --> 00:14.371
Please rev_iew the matter
of the SIX Napoleons,

00:14.410 --> 00:16.378
as the client has asked
for an update.

00:16.410 --> 00:18.173
I'll join you when I return.

00:18.210 --> 00:20.371
I advise you not to use
the refrigerator this morning.

00:20.420 --> 00:22.081
My experiments in fermentation

00:22.120 --> 00:24.418
find themselves
at a critical stage.

00:24.450 --> 00:27.283
(doorbell buzzes)

00:33.660 --> 00:34.797
Good morning.

00:34.830 --> 00:36.468
I'm calling on Sherlock Holmes.

00:36.500 --> 00:38.195
He's not here right now.

00:38.230 --> 00:39.492
I'm his partner, Joan Watson.

00:39.540 --> 00:40.393
Can I help you
with something?

00:40.440 --> 00:41.793
You look familiar.

00:41.840 --> 00:43.569
Are you a friend of Bill W?

00:43.610 --> 00:46.374
More like a friend of a friend.

00:46.410 --> 00:48.731
But you've been to meetings
at St. Olaf's

00:48.780 --> 00:51.169
with Sherlock?

00:51.210 --> 00:53.269
My name is Holder.

00:54.120 --> 00:55.417
I was wondering ifI might

00:55.450 --> 00:57.384
leave something with you.

01:04.760 --> 01:06.648
Sherlock's not really
big on hats,

01:06.700 --> 01:09.294
so I'm not sure
he's gonna want a crown.

01:09.330 --> 01:11.662
It's a coronet,
technically.

01:11.700 --> 01:14.191
Holmes calls it
my "beryl coronet."

01:14.240 --> 01:17.107
Uh, the stones are
replicas, of course.

01:17.140 --> 01:18.664
The entire thing's
a simulacrum.

01:18.710 --> 01:21.406
I'm certain it'll be
very well received.

01:21.440 --> 01:24.204
He says it reminds him
of a case from London.

01:24.250 --> 01:25.808
Um, if you don't mind
me asking,

01:25.850 --> 01:28.341
why are you giving him
a beryl coronet?

01:28.380 --> 01:30.848
Holmes did a favor for me.

01:30.890 --> 01:34.417
I have a recovering addict's
hatred for owing favors.

01:34.460 --> 01:36.348
I mailed several checks

01:36.390 --> 01:38.187
to compensate him
for his time, but

01:38.230 --> 01:39.424
they went uncashed.
This, perhaps,

01:39.460 --> 01:40.529
will settle the matter
between us.

01:40.560 --> 01:41.857
Mm-hmm.

01:41.900 --> 01:43.527
Well, you're welcome
to leave it here,

01:43.570 --> 01:45.322
but if you'd rather
give it to him in person,

01:45.370 --> 01:47.838
uh, Sherlock is actually at a
meeting at St. Olaf's right now.

01:47.870 --> 01:49.633
St. Olaf's-- you sure?

01:49.670 --> 01:51.399
I'm positive. Why?

01:51.440 --> 01:55.331
We haven't seen
Sherlock there in ages.

01:55.380 --> 01:57.439
In fact, he told us
specifically he was going

01:57.480 --> 01:59.243
to another regular session
in Greenpoint.

02:00.420 --> 02:02.149
Variety, you know.

02:02.190 --> 02:04.249
Really?
Are you sure?

02:04.290 --> 02:05.416
Well, I don't live there,

02:05.450 --> 02:07.452
but I am a regular.

02:07.490 --> 02:08.582
I'd put it at
a month since

02:08.620 --> 02:09.757
we've seen Sherlock.

02:10.760 --> 02:12.751
(cell phone chimes)

02:15.630 --> 02:18.428
Is everything
all right, my dear?

02:18.470 --> 02:20.529
Yes, yes. I just...

02:20.570 --> 02:21.889
I didn't realize
he had made the switch.

02:21.940 --> 02:22.907
Mm.

02:22.940 --> 02:25.431
Anyway, I'm happy to keep
an eye on your crown.

02:25.470 --> 02:28.439
Um, your coronet.

02:28.480 --> 02:29.799
Did Hawes tell you
what we're doing here?

02:29.850 --> 02:32.171
I did not ask.

02:32.220 --> 02:33.642
He knows we discriminate
in the work we take on,

02:33.680 --> 02:35.910
so I trust
his judgment.

02:35.950 --> 02:37.542
How was the meeting?

02:37.590 --> 02:39.410
Oh, capital.

02:39.460 --> 02:41.416
The usual, St. Olaf's?

02:41.460 --> 02:43.280
Yeah, that's right.

02:43.330 --> 02:45.286
Morning, sir.
Morning.

02:45.330 --> 02:47.525
This is Efraim Albright,

02:47.560 --> 02:49.596
He died last night
from an allergic reaction

02:49.630 --> 02:51.666
to romifidine hydrochloride.

02:51.700 --> 02:53.668
They market that as a product
called Equithesia.

02:53.700 --> 02:55.361
Animal tranquilizer
used primarily

02:55.400 --> 02:56.469
in equine surgery.

02:56.510 --> 02:57.909
It's potent stuff.

02:57.940 --> 03:00.909
I think Mr. Albright here
took it by accident,

03:00.940 --> 03:02.646
but there's a lot more
I'd like to know

03:02.680 --> 03:04.409
before I issue
the autopsy report.

03:04.450 --> 03:05.678
Man ingests horse
tranquilizer and dies.

03:05.710 --> 03:07.211
That's hardly a
problem for the ages.

03:07.250 --> 03:08.239
Why did you contact us?

03:08.280 --> 03:09.486
You didn't let me finish.

03:09.520 --> 03:11.579
I'm pretty sure
there's foul play here.

03:11.620 --> 03:12.814
I don't think Mr. Albright

03:12.860 --> 03:14.282
ingested the horse
tranquilizer directly.

03:14.320 --> 03:16.584
There appear to be
sausage casings

03:16.630 --> 03:18.825
inside Efraim
Albright's stomach.

03:18.860 --> 03:21.420
According to the
toxicology report,

03:21.460 --> 03:23.769
the meat in those casings
contains human remains.

03:23.800 --> 03:26.564
That meat is tainted
with Equithesia.

03:26.600 --> 03:28.397
So he didn't die from
taking a horse sedative.

03:28.440 --> 03:31.432
He died from eating someone
who took a horse sedative?

03:31.470 --> 03:33.279
I think so. Yes.

03:37.050 --> 03:40.645
*

04:11.050 --> 04:12.642
I'll spend some time
over in Missing Persons,

04:12.680 --> 04:14.409
but I'm pretty sure
they won't be looking

04:14.450 --> 04:16.589
for anyone who matches
the description of a hot dog.

04:16.620 --> 04:17.939
HOLMES:
Sausage.

04:17.990 --> 04:19.309
Oh, a sausage.

04:19.360 --> 04:22.420
That'll clear things up.

04:22.460 --> 04:24.348
So the question is

04:24.390 --> 04:27.029
did Albright know
he was eating someone?

04:27.060 --> 04:29.028
BELL: We've already
put him under a microscope.

04:29.060 --> 04:31.824
He donated big chunks
of his salary to charity,

04:31.870 --> 04:34.361
sings tenor in the Brooklyn
Gay Men's Choir.

04:34.400 --> 04:35.867
I'm not ruling anything out yet,

04:35.900 --> 04:38.630
but so far, Albright doesn't
strike me as a cannibal.

04:38.670 --> 04:40.001
Oh, he is a cannibal.

04:40.040 --> 04:41.678
But is he a witting one

04:41.710 --> 04:43.701
or an unwitting one?

04:43.750 --> 04:46.071
These are the contents
of his stomach.

04:46.110 --> 04:47.816
Sausage casings and all.

04:47.850 --> 04:49.886
(sniffs deeply)

04:49.920 --> 04:51.342
(gagging)

04:51.390 --> 04:52.880
Are you okay?

04:55.490 --> 04:58.379
The trick is to suppress
the gag reflex.

04:59.760 --> 05:01.318
It was an illuminating whiff.

05:01.360 --> 05:03.362
I'm sensing strong notes of

05:03.400 --> 05:04.697
anise-- you might recall...

05:04.730 --> 05:06.595
WATSON: Oh, yeah,
we traced all the major

05:06.640 --> 05:08.335
buyers of anise in the city

05:08.370 --> 05:10.031
when we were looking
into what's his name?

05:10.070 --> 05:11.401
Musgrave.

05:11.440 --> 05:14.375
As it happens...
(pants)

05:14.410 --> 05:15.877
there is one such
consumer who seems

05:15.910 --> 05:18.299
of particular interest
mmsmm.

05:20.920 --> 05:23.115
MAN:
Sorry, I'm confused.

05:23.150 --> 05:26.039
You think I sold a sausage
with a person in it?

05:26.090 --> 05:28.411
Anise is your trademark
ingredient, is it not?

05:28.460 --> 05:31.122
Yeah, but my meat comes
from cruelty-free sources.

05:31.160 --> 05:33.720
Meat which you then
grind on the premises,

05:33.760 --> 05:35.421
if your sign outside
is to be believed.

05:35.460 --> 05:36.893
Of course it is.

05:36.930 --> 05:39.967
Wait, you think
I ground somebody up?

05:40.000 --> 05:41.137
That's crazy.

05:41.170 --> 05:43.138
Do you have any proof?

05:43.170 --> 05:45.661
Other than the smell of anise
in a dead guy's stomach?

05:45.710 --> 05:47.905
No, but we would like
to investigate.

05:47.940 --> 05:49.669
Nothing happened
in my shop.

05:49.710 --> 05:51.974
Does anyone else have
access to this place?

05:52.010 --> 05:53.614
Employees with keys?

05:53.650 --> 05:56.141
I open and close the place
myself every day.

05:56.180 --> 05:59.650
We did have
a break-in last week.

05:59.690 --> 06:03.148
Somebody snapped the padlock
off the storm doors outside.

06:03.190 --> 06:05.522
They never got
upstairs, though.

06:05.560 --> 06:07.494
I keep a deadbolt
on the basement doors.

06:07.530 --> 06:09.623
The grinder's downstairs,
isn't it?

06:11.700 --> 06:14.931
Okay, so someone killed the man

06:14.970 --> 06:16.403
who Efraim Albright ate.

06:16.440 --> 06:18.704
Or woman.

06:18.740 --> 06:20.173
The victim could as easily
been female.

06:20.210 --> 06:22.576
Fine, the cannibal was
equal-opportunity.

06:22.610 --> 06:24.703
Whoever the victim was,
he, or she,

06:24.750 --> 06:25.944
was killed, dragged here,

06:25.980 --> 06:26.947
dropped into the basement,

06:26.980 --> 06:28.447
and then ground up?

06:28.480 --> 06:30.186
That's more or less
my theory, yes.

06:30.220 --> 06:31.915
And this is all based
on the fact that

06:31.950 --> 06:35.886
you smelled anise
in Albright's stomach?

06:35.920 --> 06:37.581
It's pretty thin,
don't you think?

06:37.630 --> 06:40.622
I think that a unique
set of circumstances

06:40.660 --> 06:42.696
calls for a flexible intellect

06:42.730 --> 06:44.163
to act as interpreter.

06:44.200 --> 06:45.622
Well, I-I assume

06:45.670 --> 06:46.932
we're gonna have
to make our way

06:46.970 --> 06:47.959
to that meat grinder,

06:48.000 --> 06:48.967
eventually.

06:49.000 --> 06:50.706
Yeah.

06:50.740 --> 06:51.934
You know, it's been
a while since

06:51.970 --> 06:53.198
we talked about your recovery.

06:53.240 --> 06:54.798
I mean, we used to talk
about it all the time,

06:54.840 --> 06:56.501
and now it's just
something you do.

06:56.550 --> 06:58.142
Well, we used to talk
about it all the time

06:58.180 --> 07:00.068
because you were
my sober companion.

07:00.120 --> 07:01.519
And now we're partners

07:01.550 --> 07:03.916
in the consulting detective
concern.

07:05.220 --> 07:07.017
We're also friends.
It wouldn't be so weird

07:07.060 --> 07:09.984
if we checked in with
each other once in a while.

07:10.030 --> 07:12.624
My recovery's part
of my routine.

07:12.660 --> 07:14.059
I don't discuss it with you
any more than

07:14.100 --> 07:15.192
I discuss my, uh...

07:15.230 --> 07:16.766
inhalations.

07:17.770 --> 07:19.567
Wait...

07:20.240 --> 07:22.162
What, did you find something?

07:22.200 --> 07:24.566
That's skin
and hair.

07:24.610 --> 07:28.068
That is less than
ten days old.

07:28.110 --> 07:30.078
So if someone

07:30.110 --> 07:32.249
unconscious, or barely conscious
was dragged down here,

07:32.280 --> 07:34.544
they might have banged their
head and left this behind.

07:35.850 --> 07:38.683
Both skin and hair are entirely
without pigment.

07:38.720 --> 07:40.711
Yet both are

07:40.760 --> 07:43.058
robust and springy.

07:43.090 --> 07:45.650
So whoever left this behind
wasn't old.

07:45.690 --> 07:47.226
You think he was an albino?

07:47.260 --> 07:48.818
Or she.

07:48.860 --> 07:52.261
Albinism is equally common
between both sexes.

07:52.300 --> 07:54.689
I think we should call Marcus.

07:54.740 --> 07:56.662
The parameters of
our missing persons search

07:56.710 --> 07:58.735
may just have narrowed
considerably.

08:13.020 --> 08:13.987
Watson.

08:14.020 --> 08:15.783
Hmm?

08:15.820 --> 08:16.980
It's morning.
You fell, you fell asleep.

08:17.030 --> 08:18.520
Mm, yeah.

08:18.560 --> 08:20.255
Ijust, uh...

08:20.300 --> 08:23.963
I know that Benson Durant
did not maintain

08:24.000 --> 08:25.524
his security cameras
outside his meat shop.

08:25.570 --> 08:26.867
They were all down.

08:26.900 --> 08:29.289
But I noticed there were
shops on either side

08:29.340 --> 08:31.262
that had working cameras,
so I called them

08:31.310 --> 08:32.675
and asked them
to send me footage.

08:32.710 --> 08:34.109
And you checked for albinos?

08:34.140 --> 08:35.573
Well, until I fell asleep.

08:35.610 --> 08:36.941
I didn't find anything.
I did.

08:36.980 --> 08:39.005
I've been up here
for 40 minutes looking

08:39.050 --> 08:40.779
at the footage you procured.

08:40.820 --> 08:42.708
Alas, no albinos.

08:42.750 --> 08:45.139
However, protestors
had begun to frequent

08:45.190 --> 08:46.987
the meat shop we
visited yesterday.

08:47.020 --> 08:48.556
Apparently, its owner,
Mr. Durant,

08:48.590 --> 08:49.955
had been giving a few lessons

08:49.990 --> 08:51.548
on how to butcher your own meat,

08:51.590 --> 08:52.852
and that attracted the attention

08:52.900 --> 08:54.595
of the animal rights movement.

08:54.630 --> 08:56.598
None of the protestors
suffered from albinism,

08:56.630 --> 08:57.665
however...

08:59.900 --> 09:01.561
That guy has vitiligo.

09:01.600 --> 09:03.136
Yeah, we're not
looking for an albino.

09:03.170 --> 09:04.967
We're looking for
this fellow here.

09:05.010 --> 09:06.898
And who is he?
Got no idea.

09:06.940 --> 09:09.909
The woman he's having a heated
discussion with, however,

09:09.950 --> 09:12.271
that's_a nurse at
MountVIew Hospital

09:12.310 --> 09:14.346
in Bayside.
I see the scrubs,

09:14.380 --> 09:16.348
but there's no way
to read the ID. tag

09:16.380 --> 09:18.587
from this angle.
Don't need to read it.

09:18.620 --> 09:19.917
It's orange.

09:19.960 --> 09:21.951
Mountview Hospital
is the only hospital

09:21.990 --> 09:24.823
in the five boroughs that has
orange identification badges.

09:24.860 --> 09:26.589
I sent a still
from this to Marcus,

09:26.630 --> 09:28.621
and he's trying to see
if she works there.

09:28.660 --> 09:30.298
While he's doing that,
I'm going to go out.

09:30.330 --> 09:31.365
You should wait for his call.

09:31.400 --> 09:33.288
Are you going to St. Olaf's.

09:33.340 --> 09:34.295
I find it best to tick
that particular box

09:34.340 --> 09:35.830
first thing in the morning.

09:35.870 --> 09:38.668
Quick bite to eat,
and then I'm gone.

09:44.180 --> 09:46.148
(dog barking in distance)

09:56.830 --> 09:59.128
*

10:06.670 --> 10:08.661
(musicians tuning up)

10:12.240 --> 10:13.707
(phone chimes)

10:37.770 --> 10:39.226
